The Nigeria Army said it has arrested 24 suspected kidnappers in Ondo State within two weeks of its operation around Owo and Akoko areas of Ondo State. Several persons including an army captain and a naval officer have been kidnapped along that route. Chief of Army Staff (COAS), Lieutenant General, Tukur Buratai, disclosed this when he visited the the Olowo of Owo, Oba Ajibade Gbadegesin Ogunoye III in his palace.